Why don't we show the price?

Adding the item to your cart allows Amazon to show you our price consistent with our goal of always offering you the lowest possible prices on the widest selection of products.

Adding this item won't require you to purchase the product. You can easily remove it from your cart if you decide not to buy it.

We realize that this is an inconvenience and are regularly working to educate manufacturers on how their policies impact our customers. We welcome your comments and suggestions in our forum on this topic.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Read the directions fully - rock solid once installed
    Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    Mine was a simple single switch installation. Everything was great except I skipped a key part of the instructions. Once you get the colored light to program, you must press the button twice (check the instructions) to allow programming. Once I did that, it connected instantly. I did disable my 5G network so only 2.4 was present; however, I think it would have found the 2.4. Again, my error of not following the directions was the reason for my frustration. It's been working great for over a month. The phone app is fine.

  • trailrunner
    1.0 out of 5 stars Re-connecting to WIFI is extremely difficult, takes hours of time
    Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2025
    Verified Purchase
    Eaton should improve the ease and simplicity of reconnecting to wifi. Also, re-do their app instructions so that they are correct on how to reconnect to Wifi. Instructions in app refer to a pink light. There are no pink lights on this switch in my house breaker box. I wasted hours following steps, including even switching the electrical breaker to the fan off. After two years of turning a fan on and off for 10 min every hour on the hour to ensure indoor air quality, it lost connection to Wifi. I had been using the Alexa app, but then uploaded the Eaton app (which is called the Brightlayer Home App) and did things such as delete the apps, reload the apps, and hold the darn switch down for 30 seconds for what seemed like a million times. I actually ordered a new switch after reading the other reviews about firmware problems. But after one more try at factory reset the alexa app finally finally was able to see it had reconnected, so happily I'm returning the new one. Seems like such a simple thing for them to do to improve the product as re-connecting to wifi is not such an uncommon thing. One thing for sure, after also having to work on reconnecting my printer too, I will certainly limit the smart things in my home to the minimum to avoid having to spend time reconnecting them.

  • Michael T
    5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to Install, Easy to Connect to my Network
    Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2024
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    I selected this wi-fi ready light switch to control my garage lights when coming in through the service door. When this house was built they did not install a 3-way switch for the attached garage service door. So, when I come in through the service door, it is dark and dangerous trying to navigate the 25' to the light switch. Now, this switch has saved the day.

    Installation was pretty quick. It installs like a traditional light switch, except the directions call for ataching a neutral wire to the switch. This switch is 3-way ready, but to install the second switch would be an enormous undertaking. I will be happy just using the wi-fi connection to control the lights. Attaching this switch to my home wi-fi network was also quick and easy. Keep in mind you will need to download the Eaton application to be able to control the switch from your device(s). Another thing I really like about this switch is that you can cycle back and forth with your controllers. Turn it on at the switch, then turn it off with the app, and vice versa. Of course, you can always just do it old school and use the switch to turn the lights on and off as well.

    The app is also pretty user friendly, and allows for expanding your connected devices network. Big plus there.

    I am thrilled to be able to remotely operate my garage lights! Thank you for reading my review.
